      • getAsyncDelay

        public Optional<String> getAsyncDelay()
        The length of time since the volume was last synced with the remote cluster. If the volume is not paired, this is null. Note: A target volume in an active replication state always has an async delay of 0 (zero). Target volumes are system-aware during replication and assume async delay is accurate at all times.

      • setAsyncDelay
